OL,6,FThe 'basket' measuresthe changing
OL,7,Fcost of products and services over
OL,8,Ftimeas well as thechanging tastes
OL,9,Fand habits of UK consumers.
OL,11,FThe ONS measures - on a monthly basis.
OL,13,FA surge in vinyl sales has caused for
OL,14,Fthem to be re-introduced into the
OL,15,Fbasket for the first time in 32 years.
OL,17,FOver time that list changes and the
OL,18,FONS tweaks the basket. For instance,
OL,19,Fin 1992, as CDs and cassettes
OL,20,Fincreased in popularity, the ONS
OL,21,Fremoved vinyl records from the basket.
